==Demographics==
As of the 2020 census, there were 951 people, 346 families, and 610 housing units in Lake Latonka. The median age in the CDP was 55.5 years old. 28.9% of the population was 65 years old or older, with 19.1% being between the ages of 65 and 74, 9.1% between the ages of 75 and 84, and 0.7% were 85 or older. The racial demographics of the CDP were 96.5% [[White Americans|White]], 0.1% [[African Americans|African American]], 0.5% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.1% from some other race, and 2.7% from two or more races. Hispanic and Latino people made up 1% of the population.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Lake_Latonka_CDP,_Pennsylvania?g=160XX00US4240982#race-and-ethnicity |access-date=2024-04-29 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry of the CDP was 19.6% [[German Americans|German]], 17.4% [[English Americans|English]], 14.4% [[Italian Americans|Italian]], 13.3% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 8.0% [[Scotch-Irish Americans|Scotch-Irish]], 5.7% [[French Americans|French]], 5.1% [[Polish Americans|Polish]], and 3.2% [[Hungarian Americans|Hungarian]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/table/ACSDP5Y2022.DP02?g=160XX00US4240982 |access-date=2024-04-30 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref> 2.1% of the population spoke languages other than English at home, which are Asian and Pacific Islander languages. 1.1% of the population were foreign born.<ref name=":0" />{{US Census population
